### Env Pull

- [ ] `gblockparty env pull` downloads vars and writes to `.env.local`
- [ ] Default scope is `production`
- [ ] `-s preview` fetches preview scope vars
- [ ] Secret values are written as comments (`# KEY=*** (secret -- set via dashboard)`)
- [ ] Non-secret values are written as `KEY=VALUE` pairs
- [ ] File includes header comment with scope and timestamp
- [ ] Overwrite confirmation is shown when `.env.local` exists
- [ ] `-y` flag skips overwrite confirmation
- [ ] Success message shows count of written variables
- [ ] Secret omission count is shown as a warning

### Env Push

- [ ] `gblockparty env push` reads `.env.local` and uploads vars
- [ ] Default scope is `production`
- [ ] `-s preview` pushes to preview scope
- [ ] Comment lines and empty lines are skipped during parsing
- [ ] Quoted values (`"value"` or `'value'`) have quotes stripped
- [ ] Preview shows masked values before pushing
- [ ] Success message shows count of upserted variables
- [ ] Missing `.env.local` results in an error message
- [ ] Empty `.env.local` results in a "no variables" message

### General

- [ ] Auth and project link guards work for both subcommands
- [ ] Invalid scope values are rejected
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
